Former England captain Alan Shearer says that being a pundit on Match of the Day is harder than anything he experienced in his playing days.

Shearer, who scored 30 times for his country in 64 caps and led the Three Lions on 34 occassions, insists that working on the show is tougher than playing for England.

In an interview with The Sun to mark the show's 50th anniversary, Shearer claimed that playing is easier than TV work because you don't always have to be perfect, and the experience is far more nerve-wracking.

