Shearer has been a pundit for the BBC since retiring from playing eight years ago, interrupted only by an eight-game spell as Newcastle manager in 2009. 

However he revealed that even before he worked on the show he had been an avid watcher. 

'Match of the Day was a programme I grew up watching. I always used to get home and watch my goals. It was rare I missed it.'

